ow Countries. During the second half of the fourteenth century, it underwent a particularly dramatic period in its history: the House of Leuven wason the point of disappearance, the duchy was coveted by Philip the Bold of Burgundy, who was already dreaming of extending the "Burgundian Empire" and, by a network of alliances, Brabant was drawn into the Hundred Years' War. Theauthor reviews the successive conflicts which troubled the duchy between 1356 and 1406; the different authorities which influenced the course of military operations (the duchess and the duke, their officers, and the Estates of Brabant); describes the combatants, in particular the nobility and the urban militias; considers the practical aspects of warfare; and analyses the military obligations and contracts which bound the men at arms to the duke.SERGIO BOFFA is currently researching in the department of Maps and Plans, Bibliotheque Royale de Belgique, Brussels.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMilitary art and sciencezBelgiumzBrabant (Duchy)xHistoryyMedieval, 500-1500. 0aWar and societyzBelgiumzBrabant (Duchy)xHistoryyTo 1500. 4aMedieval History. 4aMilitary History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBrabant history.  aBurgundian Empire.  aHouse of Leuven.  aHundred Years' War.  aMedieval Brabant.  aPhilip the Bold.  amilitary history.  amilitary obligations.  anobility.  aurban militias.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846151736?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846151736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846151736/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles